structure.unit: RELIGIOUS, CHARITABLE, AND EDUCATIONAL SOCIETIES -- NONSTOCK, NONPROFIT CORPORATIONS

law.text: Each corporation and each foreign corporation qualified to transact business in this Commonwealth is subject to KRS 14A.6-010.
law.history: Repealed and reenacted 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 51, sec. 85, effective July 15, 2010; amended ch. 133, sec. 23, effective July 15, 2010; and repealed and reenacted ch. 151, sec. 68, effective January 1, 2011. -- Amended 2007 Ky. Acts ch. 137, sec. 85, effective June 26, 2007. -- Created 1988 Ky. Acts ch. 23, sec. 244, effective January 1, 1989.

metadata.lrc-note: (7/15/2010). This section was amended by 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 133, and repealed and reenacted by 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 51, both effective 7/15/2010. Pursuant to Section 184 of Acts ch. 51, it was the intent of the General Assembly that the repeal and reenactment not serve to void the amendment, and these Acts do not appear to be in conflict; therefore, they have been codified together. Effective 1/1/2011, this section was also repealed and reenacted by the omnibus Kentucky Business Entity Filing Act, 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 151.
